{'book': {'publisher': 'Brill', 'synopsis': 'To deconstruct a text means to disassemble the various points of view contained within it, and to let them stand fully exposed with all their own presuppositions. When this is done, the contours of these building blocks appear so different from one another that the structural unity of the text is called into question.<br/>Biblical scholars will sense how close this process is to familiar methods of form and source criticism. Without jargon, this study sharpens and clarifies the analytical thrust behind such methods. At the same time, it offers a fresh rendering of redaction criticism, inquiring after the often contradictory motives and historical circumstances influencing the evangelists.<br/>This book thus provides an intriguing combination of the old and the new.', 'language': 'en', 'image': 'https://images.isbndb.com/covers/88/00/9789004098800.jpg', 'title_long': 'Deconstructing the New Testament (Biblical Interpretation, Vol 5)', 'edition': 1, 'dimensions': 'Height: 9.76 Inches, Length: 6.46 Inches, Weight: 1.2 Pounds, Width: 0.81 Inches', 'dimensions_structured': {'length': {'unit': 'inches', 'value': 6.46}, 'width': {'unit': 'inches', 'value': 0.81}, 'weight': {'unit': 'pounds', 'value': 1.2}, 'height': {'unit': 'inches', 'value': 9.76}}, 'pages': 201, 'date_published': '1994-04-01', 'subjects': ['Christian Books & Bibles', 'Churches & Church Leadership', 'Church History', 'Bible Study & Reference', 'Criticism & Interpretation', 'History', 'Arts & Photography', 'Architecture', 'Interior Design', 'Decorative Arts & Design', 'Interior & Home Design', 'World', 'Religious', 'Crafts, Hobbies & Home', 'Home Improvement & Design', 'Decorating & Design', 'Religion & Spirituality', 'Specialty Boutique', 'New, Used & Rental Textbooks'], 'authors': ['Seeley'], 'title': 'Deconstructing the New Testament (Biblical Interpretation, Vol 5)', 'isbn13': '9789004098800', 'msrp': 83.4, 'binding': 'Hardcover', 'isbn': '9004098801', 'isb